All 5 epics created and wired. Here's the summary:

## Polish Cycle 1 -- Epic Plan

Since all 4 reviewers crashed/timed out, I conducted an independent deep audit of the BRUTALWAV codebase. Found **25+ polish issues** across resilience, audio feedback, accessibility, and visual craft.

### Epics Created

| # | Priority | Epic ID | Title |
|---|----------|---------|-------|
| 1 | **P1** | `ba9` | QA verification via browser automation |
| 2 | P2 | `3tn` | Resilience and data safety |
| 3 | P2 | `wzc` | Live audio metering and bounce fidelity |
| 4 | P2 | `wjm` | Accessibility and interaction quality |
| 5 | P2 | `kza` | Visual craft and design system completeness |

### Dependency Graph
```
ba9 (QA) ──blocks──> 3tn (Resilience)
          ──blocks──> wzc (Metering/Bounce)  
          ──blocks──> wjm (Accessibility)
          ──blocks──> kza (Visual Craft)
```

### Key Discoveries Beyond What Reviewers Would Have Caught
- **Mixer meters are completely dead** (hardcoded 0 despite full AnalyserNode infrastructure existing)
- **Session data lost on every refresh** (in-memory storage with a "temporary" comment)
- **No ErrorBoundary anywhere** -- single component error = white screen
- **Touch input completely unsupported** on Fader/RotaryKnob (mouse-only)
- **Color contrast failures** on gray-500 labels against dark backgrounds
- **Missing keyboard shortcuts legend** -- users can't discover shortcuts

